definition:
A man of the tribe of Judah(?) living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.4.18; 
 son of: Mered (H4778)(?) and Jehudijah (H3057); 
 brother of: Jered (H3382H) and Jekuthiel (H3354); 
 half-brother of: Miriam (H4813H)(?), Shammai (H8060I)(?) and Ishbah (H3431)(?); 
 father of: Soco (H7755I)
 § Heber = "comrade"
1) the Kenite, husband of Jael, who slew Sisera by driving a nail into his temple
2) grandson of Asher from whom came the Heberites
3) father of Socho, a Judahite
4) a Benjamite
5) another Benjamite
6) a Gadite
